What are arrays used for?

Arrays are used to make and hold variables of the same object/idea/class.

What is the code for an int array?

int[] array = new int[];

What is the code for an String array?

String[] top = new String[];

What is the code for an boolean array?

boolean[] mm = new boolean[];

What is the code for an double array?

double[] d = new double[10];

How would you change the first value of the int array to 42?

int[] array = new int[42];

Of the String array to "Bob"?

String[0] = "Bob";

What does this do: private String[] dessert = new String[3];

Lets the program know there are 3 desserts Strings in the array.

What does this do: private String[] postres = {"rice pudding", "pan dulce", "bunuelos"}

Gives the name of the postres Strings.

How are they different?

The first String gives the number of dessert Strings while the other gives the names of them.

How would we replace "bunuelos" with "apple pie"?

By altering the code as such from..

private String[] postres = {"rice pudding" , "pan dulce", "bunuelos"}

...to this code.

private String[] postres = {"rice pudding" , "pan dulce", "apple pie"}
